[[File:Geonosis.jpg|thumb|250px|A Geonosian spire]]

'''Geonosian spires''' were tall, hollowed-out rock formations constructed by the [[Geonosian/Legends|Geonosians]] and used as hive-mounds, located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]].

The spires were built by the Geonosians as both permanent hive dwellings and as temporary refuge from the planet's dangerous [[Radiation/Legends|radiation]] storms. Geonosian workers constructed the vast towers from a rocky paste substance; which in turn was derived from a mix of crushed stone and the excrement of parasites called [[Phidna/Legends|Phidna]].

Upon hardening, the reddish spires would look like an extension of the terrain, camouflaging the [[Insectoid/Legends|insectoid]] species' dwelling from outsiders and making the planet appear uninhabited. In the fierce ecosystem of Geonosis, these spires also served as protection against aggressive native predators. The intentionally rough exterior belied an elegant and graceful interior architecture, consisting of flowing curves and vault-like windows.

The massive hives often extended deep underground, frequently housing vast [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|CIS]] [[Geonosis droid factories/Legends|droid foundries]] and weapons-manufacturing facilities. Below these were Geonosian birthing chambers. Even below this was the massive living areas and the Queen's chamber. The catacombs extended many miles beneath this.

There were several notable spires on Geonosis: the [[Stalgasin hive/Legends|Stalgasin hive]], which was the primary (and therefore ruling) hive, the [[Gehenbar hive/Legends|Gehenbar hive]], and the [[Golbah hive/Legends|Golbah hive]].

Just prior to the outbreak of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] stealthily entered one of the Geonosian spires, where he overheard CIS leaders discussing top-secret plans. Later, another spire was used by the CIS as a [[Geonosian War Room/Legends|command post]] during the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]], housing a battlefield holomap and presided over by [[Poggle the Lesser/Legends|Poggle the Lesser]], [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]], and several [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidian]] leaders.<ref name="SWE2">{{Film|II}}</ref> The members of [[Delta Squad/Legends|Delta Squad]] broke into a Geonosian hive and destroyed a droid factory.<ref name="SW:RC">''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando]]''</ref> During the battle, a [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone trooper]] force assaulted another spire near a force of [[Hardcell-class interstellar transport/Legends|''Hardcell''-class transports]] and Separatist bunkers.<ref name="BFI">[[Star Wars Battlefront: Prima Official Game Guide|''Star Wars Battlefront'': Prima Official Game Guide]]</ref>

